programme.title: Largest Public Land Ram in Utah 194"
programme.desc: We were very fortunate to play a roll in capturing Kyle Ekker's hunt on film. Kyle Ekker grew up in Green River Utah where he developed his love of hunting, chasing mulies on the Book Cliffs. He has worked for the Emery County Sheriff's Office for 30 years where he is currently employed as a captain. He has been a member of the Utah FNAWS for the last 10 years and through this he is able to share his passion for the outdoors & wild sheep. In December of 2015 he drew the highly coveted Rocky Mountain Bighorn Sportsman's permit. This tag gave him the opportunity to hunt sheep from the beginning of September to December 31st on almost any open units in the state. He hunted every opportunity that he had he could in pursuit of his dream ram. On November 30th things came together for him and he was able to harvest a very magnificent ram. With an unofficial green score of 194" this ram will be the largest public land ram ever killed in the state of Utah.

programme.title: What's in the Barn
programme.desc: Built in the mid-60’s by eccentric engineer “Wild Bill” Gelbke, the Road Dog was, and still is, the largest motorcycle ever built. It utilized aircraft tubing, Corvette disc brakes, and a Chevy truck differential to keep it stable. The one-off creation disappeared when Gelbke did in 1978. Outflanked once when the bike was spotted and sold to a private collector in 1995, Dale has vowed to locate the machine and make Wheels Through Time its final resting place.

Sweeting leap-frogs from dealer to dealer, busting them one at a time and moving closer to cutting off the Cayman connection. programme.desc: Nicky Barnes is Harlem's Heroin King. programme.title: Operation Greylord: Undercover In The Halls Of Injustice
programme.desc: State prosecutor Terry Hake fulfills a lifelong dream by going undercover for the FBI in Chicago. Hake works tirelessly to expose rampant corruption in the Cook County court system. Wearing a wire, he befriends and bribes crooked judges, lawyers, and bailiffs who participate in a pay-to-play perversion of justice. All told, his work results in the indictments of 92 public officials in what many call the largest government corruption case in history.

programme.title: Operation Cayman: Drug Smuggling On The High Seas
programme.desc: South Florida lawman, Jim Sweeting, partners with the DEA to infiltrate a network of drug dealers moving pot and coke via the Cayman Islands. Sweeting leap-frogs from dealer to dealer, busting them one at a time and moving closer to cutting off the Cayman connection. The operation is a minefield of bureaucratic roadblocks and gun wielding traffickers that Sweeting must juggle, while staying inside the lines of the law. If he makes a mistake and his identity is revealed, it will mean certain death.

programme.title: Operation Mr. Untouchable: Dethroning Harlem's Heroin King
programme.desc: Nicky Barnes is Harlem's Heroin King. After serving time in jail for drug dealing, Barnes has learned ways to make himself untouchable and his drug empire is such big business that even the President of the United States has taken notice. It will take patience and street smarts for DEA agent, Louis Diaz, to unravel the viper's nest of Barnes' associates and bring them all to justice - and for Diaz himself to stay alive.

programme.title: Operation Greylord: Undercover In The Halls Of Injustice
programme.desc: State prosecutor Terry Hake fulfills a lifelong dream by going undercover for the FBI in Chicago. Hake works tirelessly to expose rampant corruption in the Cook County court system. Wearing a wire, he befriends and bribes crooked judges, lawyers, and bailiffs who participate in a pay-to-play perversion of justice. All told, his work results in the indictments of 92 public officials in what many call the largest government corruption case in history.

programme.title: Operation Cayman: Drug Smuggling On The High Seas
programme.desc: South Florida lawman, Jim Sweeting, partners with the DEA to infiltrate a network of drug dealers moving pot and coke via the Cayman Islands. Sweeting leap-frogs from dealer to dealer, busting them one at a time and moving closer to cutting off the Cayman connection. The operation is a minefield of bureaucratic roadblocks and gun wielding traffickers that Sweeting must juggle, while staying inside the lines of the law. If he makes a mistake and his identity is revealed, it will mean certain death.

programme.title: Operation Mr. Untouchable: Dethroning Harlem's Heroin King
programme.desc: Nicky Barnes is Harlem's Heroin King. After serving time in jail for drug dealing, Barnes has learned ways to make himself untouchable and his drug empire is such big business that even the President of the United States has taken notice. It will take patience and street smarts for DEA agent, Louis Diaz, to unravel the viper's nest of Barnes' associates and bring them all to justice - and for Diaz himself to stay alive.

programme.title: Operation Greylord: Undercover In The Halls Of Injustice
programme.desc: State prosecutor Terry Hake fulfills a lifelong dream by going undercover for the FBI in Chicago. Hake works tirelessly to expose rampant corruption in the Cook County court system. Wearing a wire, he befriends and bribes crooked judges, lawyers, and bailiffs who participate in a pay-to-play perversion of justice. All told, his work results in the indictments of 92 public officials in what many call the largest government corruption case in history.

programme.title: Operation Cayman: Drug Smuggling On The High Seas
programme.desc: South Florida lawman, Jim Sweeting, partners with the DEA to infiltrate a network of drug dealers moving pot and coke via the Cayman Islands. Sweeting leap-frogs from dealer to dealer, busting them one at a time and moving closer to cutting off the Cayman connection. The operation is a minefield of bureaucratic roadblocks and gun wielding traffickers that Sweeting must juggle, while staying inside the lines of the law. If he makes a mistake and his identity is revealed, it will mean certain death.

programme.title: Operation Mr. Untouchable: Dethroning Harlem's Heroin King
programme.desc: Nicky Barnes is Harlem's Heroin King. After serving time in jail for drug dealing, Barnes has learned ways to make himself untouchable and his drug empire is such big business that even the President of the United States has taken notice. It will take patience and street smarts for DEA agent, Louis Diaz, to unravel the viper's nest of Barnes' associates and bring them all to justice - and for Diaz himself to stay alive.

programme.title: Operation Greylord: Undercover In The Halls Of Injustice
programme.desc: State prosecutor Terry Hake fulfills a lifelong dream by going undercover for the FBI in Chicago. Hake works tirelessly to expose rampant corruption in the Cook County court system. Wearing a wire, he befriends and bribes crooked judges, lawyers, and bailiffs who participate in a pay-to-play perversion of justice. All told, his work results in the indictments of 92 public officials in what many call the largest government corruption case in history.

programme.title: Operation Cayman: Drug Smuggling On The High Seas
programme.desc: South Florida lawman, Jim Sweeting, partners with the DEA to infiltrate a network of drug dealers moving pot and coke via the Cayman Islands. Sweeting leap-frogs from dealer to dealer, busting them one at a time and moving closer to cutting off the Cayman connection. The operation is a minefield of bureaucratic roadblocks and gun wielding traffickers that Sweeting must juggle, while staying inside the lines of the law. If he makes a mistake and his identity is revealed, it will mean certain death.

programme.title: Operation Mr. Untouchable: Dethroning Harlem's Heroin King
programme.desc: Nicky Barnes is Harlem's Heroin King. After serving time in jail for drug dealing, Barnes has learned ways to make himself untouchable and his drug empire is such big business that even the President of the United States has taken notice. It will take patience and street smarts for DEA agent, Louis Diaz, to unravel the viper's nest of Barnes' associates and bring them all to justice - and for Diaz himself to stay alive.

programme.title: Operation Greylord: Undercover In The Halls Of Injustice
programme.desc: State prosecutor Terry Hake fulfills a lifelong dream by going undercover for the FBI in Chicago. Hake works tirelessly to expose rampant corruption in the Cook County court system. Wearing a wire, he befriends and bribes crooked judges, lawyers, and bailiffs who participate in a pay-to-play perversion of justice. All told, his work results in the indictments of 92 public officials in what many call the largest government corruption case in history.

programme.desc: South Florida lawman, Jim Sweeting, partners with the DEA to infiltrate a network of drug dealers moving pot and coke via the Cayman Islands. Sweeting leap-frogs from dealer to dealer, busting them one at a time and moving closer to cutting off the Cayman connection. The operation is a minefield of bureaucratic roadblocks and gun wielding traffickers that Sweeting must juggle, while staying inside the lines of the law. If he makes a mistake and his identity is revealed, it will mean certain death.

programme.title: Operation Mr. Untouchable: Dethroning Harlem's Heroin King
programme.desc: Nicky Barnes is Harlem's Heroin King. After serving time in jail for drug dealing, Barnes has learned ways to make himself untouchable and his drug empire is such big business that even the President of the United States has taken notice. It will take patience and street smarts for DEA agent, Louis Diaz, to unravel the viper's nest of Barnes' associates and bring them all to justice - and for Diaz himself to stay alive.

programme.title: Operation Greylord: Undercover In The Halls Of Injustice
programme.desc: State prosecutor Terry Hake fulfills a lifelong dream by going undercover for the FBI in Chicago. Hake works tirelessly to expose rampant corruption in the Cook County court system. Wearing a wire, he befriends and bribes crooked judges, lawyers, and bailiffs who participate in a pay-to-play perversion of justice. All told, his work results in the indictments of 92 public officials in what many call the largest government corruption case in history.

programme.desc: Nicky Barnes is Harlem's Heroin King. After serving time in jail for drug dealing, Barnes has learned ways to make himself untouchable and his drug empire is such big business that even the President of the United States has taken notice. programme.title: Operation Greylord: Undercover In The Halls Of Injustice
programme.desc: State prosecutor Terry Hake fulfills a lifelong dream by going undercover for the FBI in Chicago. Hake works tirelessly to expose rampant corruption in the Cook County court system. Wearing a wire, he befriends and bribes crooked judges, lawyers, and bailiffs who participate in a pay-to-play perversion of justice. All told, his work results in the indictments of 92 public officials in what many call the largest government corruption case in history.

programme.title: Operation Cayman: Drug Smuggling On The High Seas
programme.desc: South Florida lawman, Jim Sweeting, partners with the DEA to infiltrate a network of drug dealers moving pot and coke via the Cayman Islands. Sweeting leap-frogs from dealer to dealer, busting them one at a time and moving closer to cutting off the Cayman connection. The operation is a minefield of bureaucratic roadblocks and gun wielding traffickers that Sweeting must juggle, while staying inside the lines of the law. If he makes a mistake and his identity is revealed, it will mean certain death.

programme.title: Operation Mr. Untouchable: Dethroning Harlem's Heroin King
programme.desc: Nicky Barnes is Harlem's Heroin King. After serving time in jail for drug dealing, Barnes has learned ways to make himself untouchable and his drug empire is such big business that even the President of the United States has taken notice. It will take patience and street smarts for DEA agent, Louis Diaz, to unravel the viper's nest of Barnes' associates and bring them all to justice - and for Diaz himself to stay alive.

programme.title: Operation Greylord: Undercover In The Halls Of Injustice
programme.desc: State prosecutor Terry Hake fulfills a lifelong dream by going undercover for the FBI in Chicago. Hake works tirelessly to expose rampant corruption in the Cook County court system. Wearing a wire, he befriends and bribes crooked judges, lawyers, and bailiffs who participate in a pay-to-play perversion of justice. All told, his work results in the indictments of 92 public officials in what many call the largest government corruption case in history.
